1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:10,000
[English subtitles are available]

2
00:01:53,539 --> 00:01:59,979
Go Ahead

3
00:02:00,140 --> 00:02:02,900
Episode 5

4
00:02:09,720 --> 00:02:10,720
I have duck necks!

5
00:02:13,840 --> 00:02:14,760
They might be cold, right?

6
00:02:14,760 --> 00:02:15,760
Then don't eat any if you think they are cold.

7
00:02:15,760 --> 00:02:16,820
Of course I'll eat.

8
00:02:17,680 --> 00:02:18,840
As I expected, you aren't wearing your coat.

9
00:02:18,840 --> 00:02:20,600
Put it on, or you might get a cold.

10
00:02:20,600 --> 00:02:21,530
Dinner is ready.

11
00:02:26,120 --> 00:02:26,560
Come on,

12
00:02:26,560 --> 00:02:27,000
Give me a coke.

13
00:02:27,000 --> 00:02:27,930
…this is for you.

14
00:02:29,200 --> 00:02:29,960
This is mine.

15
00:02:35,800 --> 00:02:37,260
Hmm, it tastes authentic!

16
00:02:37,360 --> 00:02:38,290
Is Mr. Li asleep?

17
00:02:38,520 --> 00:02:39,120
Yes,

18
00:02:39,560 --> 00:02:40,280
and he has to get up

19
00:02:40,280 --> 00:02:42,880
at 4 o'clock tomorrow morning for dough-making.

20
00:02:42,880 --> 00:02:43,880
Have you seen any meteor?

21
00:02:43,880 --> 00:02:45,360
It is said in the news that the meteor shower will come at 1 o'clock in the early morning,

22
00:02:45,360 --> 00:02:46,600
but it's still before midnight now.

23
00:02:46,600 --> 00:02:47,800
Can we wait until the meteor shower arrives?

24
00:02:47,800 --> 00:02:48,720
Two years ago,

25
00:02:48,720 --> 00:02:49,480
we waited for the meteor shower of Andromeda,

26
00:02:49,480 --> 00:02:50,560
didn't we?

27
00:02:50,760 --> 00:02:51,800
But we saw nothing

28
00:02:51,800 --> 00:02:53,360
and even got stung all over by mosquitoes.

29
00:02:53,360 --> 00:02:54,440
It is different this time.

30
00:02:54,440 --> 00:02:55,160
You see,

31
00:02:55,160 --> 00:02:55,720
it was raining then,

32
00:02:55,720 --> 00:02:57,240
while it is quite fine today.

33
00:02:57,240 --> 00:02:58,079
Besides, it seems to be

34
00:02:58,079 --> 00:02:59,280
the Leonid meteor shower

35
00:02:59,280 --> 00:03:00,240
which occurs once every 50 years.

36
00:03:00,240 --> 00:03:02,770
We will definitely see it. Let's wait and see.

37
00:03:05,840 --> 00:03:07,680
Recently I've gained much weight

38
00:03:07,680 --> 00:03:09,740
because I've eaten too much at night.

39
00:03:09,960 --> 00:03:11,020
Then just eat less.

40
00:03:11,440 --> 00:03:12,480
I'm at the age of physical growth.

41
00:03:12,480 --> 00:03:13,360
Physical growth?

42
00:03:13,360 --> 00:03:14,880
Just take a look at your tummy flab.

43
00:03:14,880 --> 00:03:15,520
Ziqiu!

44
00:03:16,200 --> 00:03:17,640
I'll knock you off!

45
00:03:25,320 --> 00:03:25,880
I wonder

46
00:03:25,880 --> 00:03:28,210
when the meteor shower is going to arrive.

47
00:03:28,240 --> 00:03:29,240
It's just a plane.

48
00:03:59,680 --> 00:04:00,760
You didn't ask your mother

49
00:04:00,760 --> 00:04:01,400
why she left you alone and went away,

50
00:04:01,400 --> 00:04:02,320
did you?

51
00:04:04,960 --> 00:04:05,480
No.

52
00:04:06,680 --> 00:04:07,810
You aren’t curious?

53
00:04:08,720 --> 00:04:09,480
No.

54
00:04:11,080 --> 00:04:11,560
OK.

55
00:04:13,040 --> 00:04:14,080
I know the reason,

56
00:04:14,080 --> 00:04:15,340
so I never wonder that.

57
00:04:17,440 --> 00:04:18,970
She didn't mean to leave me,

58
00:04:20,440 --> 00:04:21,240
but to leave all her

59
00:04:21,240 --> 00:04:22,640
past belongings behind.

60
00:04:26,840 --> 00:04:29,100
It turns out that we are just belongings.

61
00:04:30,480 --> 00:04:32,140
So you needn't think too much.

62
00:04:32,680 --> 00:04:34,400
If your mother wants to get you back,

63
00:04:34,400 --> 00:04:35,860
she will come back to do so.

64
00:04:38,480 --> 00:04:39,760
She feels free to abandon me

65
00:04:39,760 --> 00:04:40,960
or get me back.

66
00:04:41,480 --> 00:04:42,880
Who does she think she is?

67
00:04:44,760 --> 00:04:45,820
She's your mother.

68
00:04:53,880 --> 00:04:55,200
How do you feel

69
00:04:56,520 --> 00:04:59,180
about your mother coming back for you this time?

70
00:05:01,560 --> 00:05:02,520
Nothing,

71
00:05:04,080 --> 00:05:05,010
but I feel noisy.

72
00:05:08,080 --> 00:05:09,120
However,

73
00:05:09,240 --> 00:05:10,640
I feel relieved in my mind

74
00:05:11,440 --> 00:05:12,560
as I know

75
00:05:13,480 --> 00:05:15,340
that she is living a good life now.

76
00:05:18,200 --> 00:05:18,800
What?

77
00:05:19,320 --> 00:05:21,080
You've gotten mentally prepared in advance

78
00:05:21,080 --> 00:05:23,120
in case your mother suddenly comes back for you?

79
00:05:23,120 --> 00:05:24,360
Mentally prepared?

80
00:05:25,400 --> 00:05:26,400
If she comes back,

81
00:05:27,160 --> 00:05:27,880
I'll ask her

82
00:05:27,880 --> 00:05:28,880
for my dad's money

83
00:05:29,080 --> 00:05:30,410
and then drive her away.

84
00:05:31,160 --> 00:05:32,120
You think

85
00:05:32,400 --> 00:05:33,659
I'm as timid as you are?

86
00:05:35,760 --> 00:05:36,760
I hope so.

87
00:05:40,800 --> 00:05:42,060
Look, is that a meteor?

88
00:05:46,120 --> 00:05:47,320
Wake up, Jianjian, there's a meteor!

89
00:05:47,320 --> 00:05:48,120
There's a meteor

90
00:05:48,120 --> 00:05:49,120
There's a meteor!

91
00:05:49,240 --> 00:05:50,200
Get up!

92
00:05:53,520 --> 00:05:57,880
♫Light is hidden in the night by the sunset♫

93
00:05:55,360 --> 00:05:56,200
A meteor!

94
00:05:56,440 --> 00:05:58,700
This is the first time I've seen a meteor!

95
00:05:59,360 --> 00:06:04,160
♫but the sleepless stars dismantle the darkness♫

96
00:06:00,680 --> 00:06:02,080
Why do you act as a maiden?

97
00:06:02,240 --> 00:06:03,400
Making a wish doesn't cost me a penny anyway,

98
00:06:03,400 --> 00:06:05,440
and it doesn't matter even if it's not fulfilled.

99
00:06:05,440 --> 00:06:09,880
♫The night sky won't be dark♫

100
00:06:06,560 --> 00:06:07,520
Mom!

101
00:06:07,880 --> 00:06:09,680
Here I am!

102
00:06:10,280 --> 00:06:12,000
Do you see me?

103
00:06:11,200 --> 00:06:15,960
♫as long as the moonlight shines through the chinks♫

104
00:06:15,440 --> 00:06:16,640
Mom!

105
00:06:17,360 --> 00:06:20,160
♫If you ask the night sky♫

106
00:06:18,920 --> 00:06:21,320
Here I am!

107
00:06:20,480 --> 00:06:23,160
♫about the twists and turns before dawn♫

108
00:06:23,160 --> 00:06:27,680
♫It's just the past which will be gone tomorrow♫

109
00:06:24,600 --> 00:06:25,640
Mom!

110
00:06:26,280 --> 00:06:28,000
Do you see me?

111
00:06:29,000 --> 00:06:33,680
♫So silence requires not too much talk♫

112
00:06:36,120 --> 00:06:37,240
Alas, come on!

113
00:06:37,400 --> 00:06:38,240
No!

114
00:06:38,240 --> 00:06:40,120
I don't want to visit Li Jianjian's.

115
00:06:40,120 --> 00:06:41,720
We are not visiting Li Jianjian's,

116
00:06:41,720 --> 00:06:43,080
we are going to Haichao Noodles for dinner

117
00:06:43,080 --> 00:06:44,440
and visit your brother there, by the way.

118
00:06:44,440 --> 00:06:45,480
You are a liar.

119
00:06:45,480 --> 00:06:47,240
I won't trust you anymore.

120
00:06:47,800 --> 00:06:48,840
I'm a liar?

121
00:06:48,840 --> 00:06:50,000
When did I lie to you?

122
00:06:50,240 --> 00:06:51,800
You said that my brother missed me,

123
00:06:51,800 --> 00:06:53,460
and that he'd like me for sure.

124
00:06:53,480 --> 00:06:55,080
But he only likes Li Jianjian

125
00:06:55,159 --> 00:06:56,480
and ignores me!

126
00:06:59,400 --> 00:07:00,800
He likes you,

127
00:07:00,960 --> 00:07:03,040
but he can't accept this all of a sudden.

128
00:07:03,040 --> 00:07:04,440
I want to go back to Singapore

129
00:07:04,440 --> 00:07:05,920
instead of staying here!

130
00:07:05,920 --> 00:07:07,920
I don't know any schoolmates here.

131
00:07:12,840 --> 00:07:13,920
We won't be staying here

132
00:07:13,920 --> 00:07:14,840
all the time,

133
00:07:15,040 --> 00:07:17,160
and we will go back after the Spring Festival.

134
00:07:17,160 --> 00:07:17,800
Besides,

135
00:07:18,120 --> 00:07:19,360
you've told your schoolmates

136
00:07:19,360 --> 00:07:20,320
that you have an elder brother.

137
00:07:20,320 --> 00:07:21,440
If you have no photo of you and him

138
00:07:21,440 --> 00:07:22,840
when you go back next year,

139
00:07:22,840 --> 00:07:24,440
your schoolmates will think that you lied to them,

140
00:07:24,440 --> 00:07:25,120
right?

141
00:07:28,840 --> 00:07:30,280
Let's go, it's going to rain soon.

142
00:07:30,280 --> 00:07:30,880
Come on.

143
00:08:05,480 --> 00:08:06,680
You can't work it out?

144
00:08:08,240 --> 00:08:09,800
No, it's so hard.

145
00:08:12,120 --> 00:08:12,720
Let me see.

146
00:08:19,280 --> 00:08:20,360
There's a rectangular vegetable field

147
00:08:20,360 --> 00:08:21,960
which is 6 meters long and 3 meters wide.

148
00:08:21,960 --> 00:08:23,160
If it is surrounded by a fence,

149
00:08:23,160 --> 00:08:24,480
what's the length of the fence?

150
00:08:24,480 --> 00:08:26,080
Which is the length, and which is the width of the field?

151
00:08:26,080 --> 00:08:27,920
This is the length, and this is the width.

152
00:08:27,920 --> 00:08:28,480
Exactly.

153
00:08:28,760 --> 00:08:30,160
What are the length and the width of the field?

154
00:08:30,160 --> 00:08:32,080
It is 6 meters long and 3 meters wide.

155
00:08:32,080 --> 00:08:33,120
So here are two lengths

156
00:08:33,120 --> 00:08:33,960
and two widths now.

157
00:08:33,960 --> 00:08:34,909
How many meters is it

158
00:08:34,909 --> 00:08:36,570
if these numbers are added up?

159
00:08:42,120 --> 00:08:43,000
18 meters.

160
00:08:43,440 --> 00:08:44,000
Exactly.

161
00:08:45,480 --> 00:08:46,760
If one side of the field is attached to a wall,

162
00:08:46,760 --> 00:08:49,090
how many meters of the fence is remaining?

163
00:08:49,600 --> 00:08:50,360
I got it.

164
00:09:15,160 --> 00:09:17,000
It is amazing

165
00:09:17,200 --> 00:09:19,530
to see a birthmark at the same part, right?

166
00:09:20,800 --> 00:09:22,930
With the thunder as loud as it is today,

167
00:09:24,560 --> 00:09:25,480
the neighbors even couldn't hear you

168
00:09:25,480 --> 00:09:26,740
knock hard at the door.

169
00:09:31,080 --> 00:09:31,940
For many years,

170
00:09:32,680 --> 00:09:35,410
I'd dreamed repeatedly that on a thundering day,

171
00:09:36,960 --> 00:09:37,880
I couldn't find

172
00:09:39,760 --> 00:09:40,760
the way back home,

173
00:09:42,320 --> 00:09:43,760
wet all over,

174
00:09:46,080 --> 00:09:47,280
shivering with cold.

175
00:09:50,200 --> 00:09:52,200
However, I've never dreamed of this

176
00:09:52,800 --> 00:09:54,460
since I gave birth to Chengzi.

177
00:09:56,760 --> 00:09:58,640
Why did you dream of thundering?

178
00:09:59,840 --> 00:10:02,300
Because I'm afraid of being punished by God.

179
00:10:08,440 --> 00:10:09,370
Superstitious.

180
00:10:25,240 --> 00:10:26,360
How irritating!

181
00:10:26,600 --> 00:10:27,800
Why don't they leave?

182
00:10:29,920 --> 00:10:31,000
Enough,

183
00:10:31,080 --> 00:10:32,810
stop twisting the vegetables.

184
00:10:33,000 --> 00:10:35,000
Trim them quickly and let's go home.

185
00:10:35,560 --> 00:10:36,640
Go.

186
00:10:58,280 --> 00:10:59,010
Li Jianjian,

187
00:11:00,440 --> 00:11:02,100
are you having a stomachache?

188
00:11:03,360 --> 00:11:04,440
I have a headache.

189
00:11:06,600 --> 00:11:08,440
Still worried about your brother's problem?

190
00:11:08,440 --> 00:11:09,840
Don't you always say that

191
00:11:10,120 --> 00:11:10,960
a kid with a mother

192
00:11:10,960 --> 00:11:13,090
is always better off than one without?

193
00:11:14,280 --> 00:11:15,640
Yes, I do agree with that,

194
00:11:15,640 --> 00:11:16,200
but I still

195
00:11:16,200 --> 00:11:17,400
feel uneasy.

196
00:11:17,960 --> 00:11:18,960
It really was an under-punishment

197
00:11:18,960 --> 00:11:20,240
for that jerk Chengzi.

198
00:11:20,680 --> 00:11:21,320
And,

199
00:11:21,400 --> 00:11:22,320
if Ziqiu's mother

200
00:11:22,320 --> 00:11:23,560
brings me a sister too,

201
00:11:23,560 --> 00:11:24,800
I'll have to spend my lifetime

202
00:11:24,800 --> 00:11:26,530
raising kids for other people.

203
00:11:26,880 --> 00:11:28,240
Do you have to say "lifetime"?

204
00:11:28,240 --> 00:11:29,440
You are too young now.

205
00:11:33,400 --> 00:11:34,330
Oh, Li Jianjian,

206
00:11:34,640 --> 00:11:36,570
what does your brother Ziqiu like?

207
00:11:36,720 --> 00:11:38,200
He likes buns

208
00:11:38,200 --> 00:11:40,160
and noodles with sweet-and-sour ribs.

209
00:11:40,160 --> 00:11:40,840
Well,

210
00:11:41,200 --> 00:11:41,920
isn't his birthday

211
00:11:41,920 --> 00:11:42,960
around the corner?

212
00:11:42,960 --> 00:11:44,480
I must know what his favorite things are,

213
00:11:44,480 --> 00:11:46,440
so that I can buy him the right gifts.

214
00:11:46,440 --> 00:11:47,040
Oh yes.

215
00:11:47,560 --> 00:11:49,160
Next Friday is his birthday.

216
00:11:49,840 --> 00:11:51,640
You forgot something like that!

217
00:11:53,640 --> 00:11:55,400
It's not strange that I forgot it.

218
00:11:55,400 --> 00:11:56,860
But how did it occur to you?

219
00:11:58,760 --> 00:12:00,280
For things as important as birthdays,

220
00:12:00,280 --> 00:12:02,340
I've got to record them in a notebook.

221
00:12:04,320 --> 00:12:06,250
Could you tell me what Ziqiu likes?

222
00:12:23,480 --> 00:12:25,480
I think Ziqiu will like this headphone.

223
00:12:25,480 --> 00:12:27,080
His favorite color is black.

224
00:12:27,120 --> 00:12:28,380
You made a good choice.

225
00:12:28,960 --> 00:12:29,480
Yeah.

226
00:12:31,960 --> 00:12:32,560
What's the matter?

227
00:12:32,560 --> 00:12:34,420
You're not quite yourself today.

228
00:12:34,480 --> 00:12:35,840
Don't you have a sister to care about?

229
00:12:35,840 --> 00:12:37,170
Why do you care about me?

230
00:12:37,400 --> 00:12:38,060
The length.

231
00:12:38,360 --> 00:12:38,960
The width.

232
00:12:39,080 --> 00:12:39,840
The fence.

233
00:12:41,440 --> 00:12:43,160
You're jealous even about this?

234
00:12:43,160 --> 00:12:45,080
I'm jealous because of you? Come on!

235
00:12:45,080 --> 00:12:46,560
I still have Ziqiu.

236
00:12:48,280 --> 00:12:49,480
I'll pay you my share for

237
00:12:49,480 --> 00:12:51,480
the cost of the headphone back home.

238
00:13:22,960 --> 00:13:23,760
Birthday boy,

239
00:13:24,240 --> 00:13:25,440
chat with Aunt He Lan.

240
00:13:25,480 --> 00:13:26,160
I'll handle the kitchen work.

241
00:13:26,160 --> 00:13:27,520
What are you doing? I'm cooking here.

242
00:13:27,520 --> 00:13:28,580
And you can't cook.

243
00:13:28,960 --> 00:13:30,080
Besides, isn't Li Jianjian chatting

244
00:13:30,080 --> 00:13:30,800
with her?

245
00:13:31,160 --> 00:13:32,520
She's not her niece.

246
00:13:32,840 --> 00:13:33,400
Just go.

247
00:13:33,520 --> 00:13:34,560
Oh please!

248
00:13:34,560 --> 00:13:35,400
Aunt He Lan and I

249
00:13:35,400 --> 00:13:36,480
really don't have much to talk about.

250
00:13:36,480 --> 00:13:37,280
Just go.

251
00:13:38,560 --> 00:13:39,400
She came here to

252
00:13:39,400 --> 00:13:40,860
celebrate your birthday.

253
00:13:41,000 --> 00:13:42,440
Just talk about some casual stuff.

254
00:13:42,440 --> 00:13:42,920
Go.

255
00:13:43,200 --> 00:13:43,760
OK.

256
00:13:44,240 --> 00:13:45,560
Take the fruit slices on the table

257
00:13:45,560 --> 00:13:46,200
to her.

258
00:13:50,880 --> 00:13:52,340
Don't do the cutting work.

259
00:13:52,400 --> 00:13:53,640
You may cut your finger.

260
00:13:53,640 --> 00:13:54,840
Wash the coriander.

261
00:13:55,080 --> 00:13:55,680
OK.

262
00:14:00,560 --> 00:14:01,680
Miss Li!

263
00:14:03,160 --> 00:14:04,420
Just call me Jianjian.

264
00:14:07,440 --> 00:14:08,160
Jianjian.

265
00:14:08,240 --> 00:14:08,680
OK.

266
00:14:08,880 --> 00:14:10,040
Won't doing this stuff

267
00:14:10,040 --> 00:14:11,240
affect your studies?

268
00:14:11,960 --> 00:14:12,640
No, it won't.

269
00:14:12,640 --> 00:14:15,080
My usual academic performance isn't great anyway.

270
00:14:15,080 --> 00:14:15,740
Aunt He Lan.

271
00:14:16,240 --> 00:14:17,160
Here, Li Jianjian,

272
00:14:17,160 --> 00:14:18,240
fresh apple slices.

273
00:14:18,240 --> 00:14:18,840
Have some.

274
00:14:21,120 --> 00:14:22,160
Jianjian, go ahead.

275
00:14:22,160 --> 00:14:22,960
Your hands are dirty.

276
00:14:22,960 --> 00:14:24,400
There're toothpicks here, right?

277
00:14:24,400 --> 00:14:25,240
Look what a mess you've made on the table.

278
00:14:25,240 --> 00:14:26,360
Clean it up later yourself.

279
00:14:26,360 --> 00:14:26,920
OK.

280
00:14:42,880 --> 00:14:44,160
Aunt He Lan, whatever you want to say,

281
00:14:44,160 --> 00:14:44,880
can't you just

282
00:14:44,880 --> 00:14:45,680
say it there?

283
00:14:46,160 --> 00:14:46,960
Sit down.

284
00:14:47,440 --> 00:14:47,920
OK.

285
00:14:51,760 --> 00:14:52,640
Just now,

286
00:14:52,760 --> 00:14:53,200
why did you

287
00:14:53,200 --> 00:14:54,860
